This repo belongs to the **tylerhuntington222** GitHub account. Do **not** run `gh auth switch`.

## Git push / pull / fetch

Use the repo remote as configured. It points at the `github-personal` SSH host alias, which authenticates as tylerhuntington222:

```bash
git push origin main
```

Do not change `origin` back to HTTPS for this repo.

## GitHub CLI (`gh`)

Use the repo wrapper so only that command runs as tylerhuntington222:

```bash
./scripts/gh222 pr create ...
./scripts/gh222 api repos/tylerhuntington222/tyler-t-huntington-site/...
```

Equivalent one-off form:

```bash
GH_TOKEN="$(gh auth token --user tylerhuntington222)" gh pr create ...
```

## Why

Other agents on this machine rely on the global active GitHub account staying **tylerhuntington**. Repo-local SSH remote + per-command `GH_TOKEN` keep account selection scoped to this project only.
